Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel @onion{1}(half grated, half thinly sliced).

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid (¾ cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Return potatoes to #pot{} and mash with half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and 2 TBSP @butter{4%tablespoon} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{3%teaspoon} and @black pepper{1%teaspoon}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. (Save peas for another use.)

While potatoes cook, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, grated onion, @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @nutmeg{½%teaspoon}, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and pepper.

Form mixture into 10-12 1 1/2-inch meatballs (20-24 meatballs for 4) and place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt 1 TBSP butter in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @peas{1%ounce} and cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir peas. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Swap in asparagus for peas.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add sliced onion and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is browned and softened, ~{3-6%minutes}.

Add 1 TBSP butter and cook, whisking, until butter melts.

Sprinkle @flour{1%tablespoon} over onion; cook, whisking constantly, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Slowly whisk 1 cup water into pan with onion. Add @beef stock concentrate{2}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, and ¼ tsp nutmeg; whisk until cream cheese melts and gravy has thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add meatballs to pan with gravy; toss to coat.

Divide mashed potatoes between #bowls{}. Top with meatballs and peas. Serve.

Top meatballs with asparagus.